economy any more.

Last week I got an e-mail offer from Citi for a &quot;Line of Credit&quot;
card. Not a credit card, but a &quot;Line of Credit&quot; card. I applied
on-line. I got approved. I got a welcom e-mail. It said that
they'd be sending me the papers in ~10 days.

Next day I got _another_ welcome e-mail, with my name mis-spelled
(OK, I might have done it, I just don't know for sure). But there
was an 800 number to call in the message, so I did. There, they
know *nothing* about any  &quot;Line of Credit&quot; card.

I started thinking that I might have been &quot;phished&quot;, and said so.
Right away they transferred me to the fraud dept. There, we got
it straightened out, and got the spelling corrected, and the
_correct_ number for the &quot;Line of Credit&quot; card people.

So, on the one hand we have one hand not knowing what *it* is
doing, and on the other hand, well, I just don't know what the
other hand is doing. We'll see.

Ths point being, however ios that it's getting harder &amp; harder to
put together anything that will hold up.
