Bill Turlock wrote:
&gt; I agree. 'Cept you lose cred cred for cancelling a card, it goes
&gt; on your credit report as some kind of negative.
">

Not as such. The negative aspect is that you will lose available credit,
which counts towards your used credit/available credit ratio.

So if you have a few cards and/or you cancel one that has a high credit
limit, your balances are going to be higher percentage of your total
credit limits.

That's another reason to have more than one card with higher credit
limits than you ever imagine using.

Though if the card has no annual fee, there's no need to cancel it. Just
don't use it. Or use it once or twice a year, so it won't be canceled as
inactive.
