referred to a &quot;Home Equity Line of Credit&quot;.  I agreed with her and
wrote about my experiences with HELOCs.  I have both a line of credit
that's based on my good record alone (prime plus 2.5%) and one that's
a second mortgage on my home (prime).  Both of mine are organized like
checking accounts.  I can get to both of mine from any Interac branded
ATM and almost any retailer in Canada.  On our Galveston visit, we
couldn't get to Interac from the cashier, but the ATM near the door
could get at my line of credit just like any other ATM card linked
account.  Some ATMs show the five-digit negative amount as a positive
balance, some as negative.

